mptoms with temporary coverage.",traditional:{label:"Traditional creams",heading:"Surface coverage approach",items:["Temporarily fills or masks lines","Hydration-based plumping only","Results wash away with cleansing","Does not support cellular processes","Requires daily application for minimal effect"]},product:{label:"Precision Collagen Activation Syringe",heading:"Biological correction approach",items:["Supports the body's own collagen production","Dual-action: immediate + long-term","Helps release muscle tension in treated areas","Supports fluid balance and visible refinement","Weekly treatment with as-needed enhancement option"]}},faq:[{q:"Is this an injectable treatment?",a:"No. Precision Collagen Activation Syringe is a non-injectable, external application treatment. The applicator resembles a syringe for precision delivery, but no needle or injection is involved. It is a cream-based formulation designed for targeted external use."},{q:"Will I see results from the first use?",a:"Precision Collagen Activation Syringe is designed with a dual-action approach. Many users report visible refinement from the first application that may last throughout the day. The long-term cellular support builds progressively with consistent weekly use. Individual results may vary."},{q:"How often should I use it?",a:"For long-term cellular support, apply once per week. For immediate visible enhancement before important occasions, use as-needed 30–60 minutes prior. Do not use more than once per day."},{q:"How does it differ from a regular cream or serum?",a:"Precision Collagen Activation Syringe is an Advanced Skin Correction Treatment — a distinct category. Unlike moisturisers that hydrate the surface or serums that deliver nutrients, this treatment is designed to help your body address visible concerns by supporting collagen production, muscle release, and fluid balance."},{q:"What is the Refill and why do I need the Precision Collagen Activation Syringe first?",a:"Precision Collagen Activation Syringe is your key to the Zero Lines ecosystem. The Refill cartridge is designed exclusively for use with the Precision Collagen Activation Syringe applicator and is priced significantly lower. By purchasing the Precision Collagen Activation Syringe, you gain access to continued treatment through affordable Refill cartridges."},{q:"How long does one Syringe unit last?",a:"One Syringe provides approximately 60 applications. With once-weekly use, this is designed to last approximately one year. With additional as-needed use, duration will vary."},{q:"Is it suitable for sensitive skin?",a:"The formulation is designed for external facial application and is suitable for most skin types. If you have sensitive skin or experience any irritation, discontinue use and consult a healthcare professional."},{q:"What happens if I stop using it?",a:"The immediate visible refinement effect is temporary and will diminish when use is discontinued. The progressive benefits from consistent weekly use may be maintained for a period after stopping. Individual experiences may vary."}],cta:{title:"Your key to the ecosystem",description:"Purchase the Precision Collagen Activation Syringe to enter the Zero Lines ecosystem. Gain access to the complete Longevity Protocol and the ability to purchase affordable Refill cartridges for continued treatment."}},serum:{slug:"serum",name:"BioSignal Facial Serum",subtitle:"BioSignal Daily Treatment",eyebrow:"Step 03 · Daily Treatment",heroDescription:"A concentrated daily treatment serum delivering bioactive peptides and hydrolyzed collagen deep into the dermal layer for comprehensive skin renewal support.",price:345,image:"/assets/product-serum.jpg",overview:{heading:"A different category of daily treatment",intro:"The Serum is not a standard hydrator or vitamin C drop. It is a concentrated daily treatment delivering bioactive compounds designed to support the skin's skin renewal processes at the dermal level.",cards:[{title:"Deep dermal delivery",body:"Formulated with a molecular weight profile designed to support penetration beyond the surface layer, delivering active compounds where skin renewal occurs."},{title:"Daily cellular support",body:"A daily treatment that works progressively to support collagen architecture, skin firmness, and the visible appearance of refined texture over time."},{title:"Protocol foundation",body:"The Serum is the cornerstone of the Longevity Protocol — the daily treatment that connects the weekly exfoliation step to the protective moisturising steps."}]},whatItIs:{heading:"What this product is designed to support",benefits:["Helps support the visible appearance of skin firmness and elasticity over time","Designed to work at the dermal level to support skin renewal activity","Formulated to promote a more refined, smoother-looking skin texture","Supports the skin's natural collagen architecture with botanical extracts","Daily treatment designed for comprehensive facial and neck application","Suitable for external application on facial and neck skin"]},howItWorks:{heading:"How it works",activation:{title:"Delivery mechanism",paragraphs:["The Serum utilises a botanical peptide complex designed to mimic the skin's natural signalling molecules. These peptides communicate with fibroblast cells, supporting the processes involved in collagen synthesis and tissue repair.","Combined with hydrolyzed collagen, the formulation works at the skin level to support the skin's structural renewal. With consistent daily application, this supports progressive improvement in the visible appearance of firmness, texture, and overall skin quality."]},ingredients:{title:"Key ingredient system",items:[{name:"Botanical Peptide Complex",description:"Watermelon extract contributes to skin hydration and provides a fresh, revitalising sensation."},{name:"hydrolyzed collagen",description:"Hydrolyzed collagen — a naturally-derived biopolymer that supports the skin's natural tissue repair and skin renewal mechanisms."},{name:"Dermal Delivery System",description:"A lightweight aqueous base of Pyrenean mineral water that helps deliver botanical extracts and maintain skin hydration."}]}},protocol:{heading:"Usage protocol",intro:"The Serum follows a structured daily application protocol. Consistency is essential for progressive cellular support.",steps:[{title:"Daily application",body:"Apply 3–4 drops to cleansed face and neck every morning and/or evening. The protocol recommends twice-daily application for optimal results."},{title:"Press, don't rub",body:"Gently press the serum into the skin using your fingertips. Pressing supports absorption without pulling or stretching the skin."},{title:"Allow absorption",body:"Wait approximately 1 minute before applying your Environmental Shield Day Cream or Renewal and Repair Night Cream. This allows the active compounds to begin their work."},{title:"Long-term commitment",body:"Cellular renewal is a gradual process. Consistent daily use for a minimum of 8–12 weeks supports the progressive refinement the protocol is designed to achieve."}],summary:[{label:"Frequency",value:"Twice daily (AM/PM)"},{label:"Amount",value:"3–4 drops"},{label:"Application",value:"Face and neck"},{label:"Absorption time",value:"~1 minute"},{label:"Protocol position",value:"Step 3 of 6"}]},important:{heading:"Important guidelines",intro:"Follow these guidelines to ensure optimal conditions for the daily treatment protocol.",do:["Apply to cleansed, slightly damp skin","Use the press-and-hold technique for absorption","Apply to both face and neck","Wait 1 minute before following with moisturiser","Use consistently — twice daily for optimal results"],avoid:["Rubbing or dragging the skin during application","Applying too much — 3–4 drops is sufficient","Layering with other active serums at the same time","Skipping days — consistency is key","Applying to broken or irritated skin"],warning:{title:"External use only",body:"The Serum is designed exclusively for external facial and neck application. Avoid contact with eyes. If irritation occurs, discontinue use and consult a healthcare professional."}},comparison:{heading:"Why it's different",intro:"The Serum represents a distinct approach to daily treatment — cellular-level support rather than surface-level hydration.",traditional:{label:"Standard serums",heading:"Surface-level hydration or antioxidants",items:["Primarily hydrates or provides antioxidant protection","Works on the skin surface","Visible results are often temporary","May not support dermal renewal","General-purpose formulation"]},product:{label:"The Serum",heading:"Dermal-level cellular support",items:["Supports skin renewal at the dermal level","Botanical extracts signal fibroblasts","Progressive, longer-term visible improvement","hydrolyzed collagen supports tissue repair mechanisms","Designed as a protocol cornerstone"]}},faq:[{q:"How long before I see results?",a:"The Serum is designed for progressive cellular support. While some users report visible improvements in skin texture and radiance within a few weeks, the full benefits of skin renewal build over 8–12 weeks of consistent twice-daily use. Individual results may vary."},{q:"Can I use it with other serums?",a:"The Serum is designed as a comprehensive treatment within the Longevity Protocol. We recommend using it as your primary active serum. If you wish to incorporate other products, apply them at a different time of day."},{q:"Should I use it morning or evening?",a:"For optimal results, the protocol recommends twice-daily application — morning and evening. If you prefer once daily, evening application allows the active compounds to work during the skin's natural overnight renewal cycle."},{q:"How long does one bottle last?",a:"With twice-daily use of 3–4 drops, one bottle is designed to last approximately 6–8 weeks."},{q:"Is it oily or heavy?",a:"The Serum is formulated with a lightweight, fast-absorbing texture. It is designed to penetrate q